line JSON handled correctly |\\n| 2 | `e2e/agents/kiro.go` | WaitFor ignores pattern | **Intentional** — prevents false matches from TUI echo |\\n| 3 | `kiro/lifecycle.go` | Stale session ID cache | **REAL BUG** — cache never cleared at stop |\\n| 4 | `implement.md` | Typo \\\"develpoment\\\" | **False positive** — already correct |\\n| 5 | `kiro/AGENT.md` | Wrong hook path | **False positive** — doc is accurate |\\n| 6 | `kiro/kiro_test.go` | Incomplete DetectPresence test | **False positive** — test is complete |\\n| 7 | `kiro/lifecycle.go` | Cache never cleared (same as #3) | **REAL BUG** (duplicate of #3) |\\n| 8 | `manual_commit_hooks.go` | Fast path auto-links human commits | **Intentional** — ACTIVE session = agent is working |\\n| 9 | `scripts/test-kiro-agent-integration.sh` | Wrong capture.json format | **REAL BUG** — bare hook map vs `kiroAgentFile` |\\n| 10 | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | Kiro fails without auth | **False positive** — properly gated behind AWS OIDC |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Changes to Make\\n\\n### 1. Clear session ID cache in `parseStop` (lifecycle.go)\\n\\n**Bug:** The `kiro-active-session` cache file persists after `parseStop`. If a new session starts and `agentSpawn` doesn't fire (e.g., Kiro is resumed), `parseUserPromptSubmit` reads the stale ID from the previous session.\\n\\n**Fix:** Add `k.clearCachedSessionID(ctx)` at the end of `parseStop` (after reading it). Add a helper method:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (k *KiroAgent) clearCachedSessionID(ctx context.Context) {\\n    cachePath := k.sessionIDCachePath(ctx)\\n    if err := os.Remove(cachePath); err != nil && !os.IsNotExist(err) {\\n        logging.Warn(ctx, \\\"kiro: failed to clear session ID cache\\\", \\\"err\\\", err)\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go`\\n- Add `clearCachedSessionID` method\\n- Call it at end of `parseStop` (after line 174, before the return)\\n- Add test: `TestSessionIDCaching_StopClearsCache` — verify cache file is removed after stop\\n\\n### 2. Fix capture.json format in test script\\n\\n**Bug:** `scripts/test-kiro-agent-integration.sh` writes hooks at top-level of `capture.json`, but Kiro expects `kiroAgentFile` format with `name`, `tools`, and `hooks` nesting.\\n\\n**Fix:** Wrap the hooks in the correct structure:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"capture\\\",\\n  \\\"tools\\\": [\\\"shell\\\"],\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"agentSpawn\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"cat > ...\\\"}],\\n    \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"cat > ...\\\"}],\\n    \\\"stop\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"cat > ...\\\"}]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**File:** `scripts/test-kiro-agent-integration.sh` (lines 53-59)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nThe new `TestSessionIDCaching_StopClearsCache` test will verify the cache clearing behavior.\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/7d500980-585e-442f-839d-e2308b5d8e1f.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"33b35275-7c2e-467d-b86b-fd9e9714e1d5\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T20:29:57.346Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix PR Review Comments on Kiro Branch\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nPR #554 (Kiro agent integration) received 10 inline comments from Cursor Bugbot and Copilot. After investigating each, **2 are real code bugs** and **1 is a script format bug**. The rest are false positives or intentional design choices.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Triage Summary\\n\\n| # | File | Claim | Verdict |\\n|---|------|-------|---------|\\n| 1 | `kiro/kiro.go` | ChunkTranscript JSONL corrupts JSON | **False positive** — 50MB threshold + single-line JSON handled correctly |\\n| 2 | `e2e/agents/kiro.go` | WaitFor ignores pattern | **Intentional** — prevents false matches from TUI echo |\\n| 3 | `kiro/lifecycle.go` | Stale session ID cache | **REAL BUG** — cache never cleared at stop |\\n| 4 | `implement.md` | Typo \\\"develpoment\\\" | **False positive** — already correct |\\n| 5 | `kiro/AGENT.md` | Wrong hook path | **False positive** — doc is accurate |\\n| 6 | `kiro/kiro_test.go` | Incomplete DetectPresence test | **False positive** — test is complete |\\n| 7 | `kiro/lifecycle.go` | Cache never cleared (same as #3) | **REAL BUG** (duplicate of #3) |\\n| 8 | `manual_commit_hooks.go` | Fast path auto-links human commits | **Intentional** — ACTIVE session = agent is working |\\n| 9 | `scripts/test-kiro-agent-integration.sh` | Wrong capture.json format | **REAL BUG** — bare hook map vs `kiroAgentFile` |\\n| 10 | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | Kiro fails without auth | **False positive** — properly gated behind AWS OIDC |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Changes to Make\\n\\n### 1. Clear session ID cache in `parseStop` (lifecycle.go)\\n\\n**Bug:** The `kiro-active-session` cache file persists after `parseStop`. If a new session starts and `agentSpawn` doesn't fire (e.g., Kiro is resumed), `parseUserPromptSubmit` reads the stale ID from the previous session.\\n\\n**Fix:** Add `k.clearCachedSessionID(ctx)` at the end of `parseStop` (after reading it). Add a helper method:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (k *KiroAgent) clearCachedSessionID(ctx context.Context) {\\n    cachePath := k.sessionIDCachePath(ctx)\\n    if err := os.Remove(cachePath); err != nil && !os.IsNotExist(err) {\\n        logging.Warn(ctx, \\\"kiro: failed to clear session ID cache\\\", \\\"err\\\", err)\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go`\\n- Add `clearCachedSessionID` method\\n- Call it at end of `parseStop` (after line 174, before the return)\\n- Add test: `TestSessionIDCaching_StopClearsCache` — verify cache file is removed after stop\\n\\n### 2. Fix capture.json format in test script\\n\\n**Bug:** `scripts/test-kiro-agent-integration.sh` writes hooks at top-level of `capture.json`, but Kiro expects `kiroAgentFile` format with `name`, `tools`, and `hooks` nesting.\\n\\n**Fix:** Wrap the hooks in the correct structure:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"capture\\\",\\n  \\\"tools\\\": [\\\"shell\\\"],\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"agentSpawn\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"cat > ...\\\"}],\\n    \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"cat > ...\\\"}],\\n    \\\"stop\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"cat > ...\\\"}]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**File:** `scripts/test-kiro-agent-integration.sh` (lines 53-59)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nThe new `TestSessionIDCaching_StopClearsCache` test will verify the cache clearing behavior.\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"33b35275-7c2e-467d-b86b-fd9e9714e1d5\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"de3ab060-7850-492f-bca7-ec08963c00e1\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"joyful-chasing-mochi\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01Q99TJBmzTTZsR39sM3numP\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Let me start by reading the relevant files to understand the current code before making changes.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":23277,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":31694,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":23277},\"output_tokens\":10,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYifzuPC59WEzm2R3WUeR\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"088e4833-a57c-4fae-890e-1317434f8b59\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T20:30:01.021Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"088e4833-a57c-4fae-890e-1317434f8b59\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"de3ab060-7850-492f-bca7-ec08963c00e1\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"g